📘 Java Arrays Practice Questions (Basic → Advanced)
🟢 Basic Level (1–5)
Write a program to declare an array of 5 integers and print all its elements.
Write a program to find the sum of all elements in an array.
Write a program to find the average of array elements.
Write a program to find the largest element in an array.
Write a program to find the smallest element in an array.
🟡 Intermediate Level (6–10)
Write a program to count even and odd numbers in an array.
Write a program to search a given element in an array (Linear Search).
Write a program to reverse an array.
Write a program to find the second largest element in an array.
Write a program to sort an array in ascending order without using built-in methods.
🔴 Advanced Level (11–15)
Write a program to remove duplicate elements from an array.
Write a program to merge two arrays into a third array.
Write a program to rotate an array to the left by one position.
Write a program to rotate an array to the right by one position.
Write a program to find the frequency of each element in an array.
🏆 Challenge Level (16–20)
Write a program to find the missing number in an array containing numbers from 1 to N.
Write a program to find duplicate elements in an array.
Write a program to find the intersection of two arrays.
Write a program to find the union of two arrays.
Write a program to find the maximum difference between two elements such that the larger element appears after the smaller element